Interface Flooring Systems Incsaid it has filed for an offering of 2,800,000 Class A commonshares through underwriters led by Robinson-Humphrey Co Inc andPaineWebber Group Inc &lt;PWJ>.    The company said as previously announced, it will useproceeds to finance a tender offer to acquire the 50 pct ofDebron Investments PLC it does not already own and to repaydebt.  It said if it acquires all of Debron, it will repurchase900,000 Class A shares now owned by Debron and hold them in itstreasury. Reuter&#3;